The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for quantification, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The data-sets used in the paper are related to marine ecology, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to subfields such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) that deal with image and pattern recognition. The paper also discusses the evaluation of different quantification methods, which may be relevant to subfields such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) that deal with algorithm evaluation and optimization.
